latestPosts.caption:
This year, I celebrated with a slightly heavy heart. With everything constantly moving around me, I wasn’t quite ready to feel a year older. Life’s been a whirlwind..juggling between work, content, emotions, expectations, friendships & relationships. It’s easy to make it look effortless, but the truth is, it gets overwhelming.

Honestly, I didn’t even feel like celebrating this year. But then, it would be unfair to the people who’ve been there for me, who’ve shown up with love. So, Thank you, from the deepest part of my heart, to everyone who sent wishes, stayed, loved and who chose to celebrate me even when I struggled to celebrate myself.

And even in all the chaos, I’m grateful. This year brought so much..creating content more consistently, monetising my work, meeting beautiful souls, and receiving opportunities I once only wished for. It’s been beautiful… and exhausting. Somewhere between chasing growth and trying to keep it all together, I forgot to just be.

So, here’s to slowing down when needed, being softer with ourselves, and accepting that we don’t always have to have it all figured out.

Afterall, we’re only 20 something :)
